headline: Is It Time to Just Buy Nike Stock as a Turnaround Takes Hold?
summary: Nike shares jumped higher as the company indicated the worst is over.  It's been frustrating to be a Nike (NYSE: NKE) investor the past few years, but investors cheered after new CEO Elliott Hill indicated that the worst was now behind the company after it reported its fiscal fourth quarter results.  Nike shares surged on the results, which topped low expectations, although the stock is still down on the year and more than 20% lower over the past five years.
